# apt-get install virtualbox

# apt-get install vagrant

Add a Vagrant box image for Ubuntu 14.04

$ vagrant box add ubuntu/trusty64



$ mkdir -p vagrant_machines/vm1/vm
$ mkdir -p vagrant_machines/vm1/data



Now create a Vagrant file which will use the ubuntu/trusty64 box.

...vagrant_machines/vm1/vm$ vagrant init ubuntu/trusty64
